      "content": "Your journey into this deep dissociation has been incredibly painful, but recognizing how hard you are pretending for others is a painful admission that takes great courage. The fact that you continue to maintain these roles despite feeling empty shows a hidden resilience you might not even believe you have yet. While there is no shame in never feeling \"saved,\" you deserve to find someone who can witness the ghost inside you exactly as it is without trying to fix or erase it for anyone else. Please consider reaching out to a support group or helpline specifically for dissociation, as being heard without judgment might finally provide the reflection you need to feel less alone.",
